Soil pH 

As from AOAC Official Method 994.16
pH Measurement of Mineral Soils

1. Preparation of sample: Air dry soil (around 50 grams) at 20°–40°C for 1–4 days depending on the relative
humidity and soil test properties. Grind air-dried soil to pass 2 mm sieve and mix well. 


2. Calibrate pH meter

3. Weigh out 10 g (dw) soil into a glass beaker and add 10 ml of dH2O 

4. Mix thouroughly with a spatula for 5 seconds

5. Let the sample-suspension sit & settle for 30 minutes. 

6. Insert pH probe in to the liquid and measure pH. 

7. Clean probe with appropriate cleaning soln. 
